This paper is about developing a personalized dialogue system using transfer learning and reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses reinforcement learning and transfer learning, which are also covered in the sub-categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the dialogue system, which can be considered as a sub-topic of "Software Engineering" (cs.SE) or "Human-Computer Interaction" (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of POMDPs, which are a type of decision-making model, and can be considered as a sub-topic of "Systems and Control" (cs.SD).
